    <text>
        <body>
            <entry xml:id="entry_kæsyn" xml:lang="os">
                <form xml:lang="os-x-iron" type="lemma"><orth>kæsyn</orth><form type="participle"
                            ><orth>kast</orth></form></form>
                <form xml:lang="os-x-digor" type="dialectal"><orth>kæsun</orth><form
                        type="participle"><orth>kast</orth></form></form>
                <sense><sense><abv:tr xml:lang="ru">
                            <q>смотреть</q>
                        </abv:tr><abv:tr xml:lang="en">
                            <q>to look</q>
                        </abv:tr></sense><sense><abv:tr xml:lang="ru">
                            <q>читать</q>
                        </abv:tr><abv:tr xml:lang="en">
                            <q>to read</q>
                        </abv:tr></sense><sense><abv:tr xml:lang="ru">
                            <q>ждать</q>
                        </abv:tr><abv:tr xml:lang="en">
                            <q>to wait</q>
                        </abv:tr></sense><sense><abv:tr xml:lang="ru">
                            <q>казаться</q>
                        </abv:tr><abv:tr xml:lang="en">
                            <q>to seem</q>
                        </abv:tr></sense></sense>
                <abv:exampleGrp>
                    <abv:example>
                        <quote>mæ īw cæstæj k˳y bakæsīn, mæ xury cæst, dæwmæ</quote>
                        <abv:tr xml:lang="ru">
                            <q>хоть бы мне взглянуть одним глазом, мое солнышко, на тебя</q>
                        </abv:tr>
                        <abv:tr xml:lang="en">
                            <q>if only I could look with one eye at you, my sunshine</q>
                        </abv:tr>
                        <bibl><ref type="bibl" target="#src_Коста"
                            /><biblScope>110</biblScope></bibl>
                    </abv:example>
                    <abv:example>
                        <quote>xūr yskastī</quote>
                        <abv:tr xml:lang="ru">
                            <q>солнце взошло</q>
                        </abv:tr>
                        <abv:tr xml:lang="en">
                            <q>the sun rose</q>
                        </abv:tr>
                    </abv:example>
                    <abv:example>
                        <quote>tyzmægæj mæm ma kæs</quote>
                        <abv:tr xml:lang="ru">
                            <q>не гляди на меня сурово</q>
                        </abv:tr>
                        <abv:tr xml:lang="en">
                            <q>do not look severely at me</q>
                        </abv:tr>
                        <bibl><ref type="bibl" target="#src_Коста"/><biblScope>14</biblScope></bibl>
                    </abv:example>
                    <abv:example>
                        <quote>fækæsyn a-be-tæ, fæfyssyn be-ve-tæ</quote>
                        <abv:tr xml:lang="ru">
                            <q>читаю а-бе, пишу бе-ве</q>
                        </abv:tr>
                        <abv:tr xml:lang="en">
                            <q>I am reading a-be, I am writing be-ve</q>
                        </abv:tr>
                        <bibl><ref type="bibl" target="#src_Коста"
                            /><biblScope>115</biblScope></bibl>
                    </abv:example>
                    <abv:example>
                        <quote>am mæm fækæs</quote>
                        <abv:tr xml:lang="ru">
                            <q>подожди меня здесь</q>
                        </abv:tr>
                        <abv:tr xml:lang="en">
                            <q>wait for me here</q>
                        </abv:tr>
                    </abv:example>
                    <abv:example>
                        <quote>nybbar myn, kæd īw dæm mæ zaræg kæwægaw fækæsa mijiag</quote>
                        <abv:tr xml:lang="ru">
                            <q>прости мне, если моя песня покажется тебе подобной плачу</q>
                        </abv:tr>
                        <abv:tr xml:lang="en">
                            <q>forgive me, if my song will seem like a cry to you</q>
                        </abv:tr>
                        <bibl><ref type="bibl" target="#src_Коста"/><biblScope>11</biblScope></bibl>
                    </abv:example>
                    <abv:example>
                        <quote>axæm card dæwmæ dær xūdinag kæsæd</quote>
                        <abv:tr xml:lang="ru">
                            <q>такая жизнь и тебе пусть кажется постыдной</q>
                        </abv:tr>
                        <abv:tr xml:lang="en">
                            <q>let this life seem shameful for you as well</q>
                        </abv:tr>
                        <bibl><ref type="bibl" target="#src_Коста"/><biblScope>94</biblScope></bibl>
                    </abv:example>
                    <abv:example>
                        <quote>tærīǧæd æm kæsync</quote>
                        <abv:tr xml:lang="ru">
                            <q>eму их жалко</q>
                        </abv:tr>
                        <abv:tr xml:lang="en">
                            <q>he is sorry for them</q>
                        </abv:tr>
                        <bibl><ref type="bibl" target="#src_Брит."/><biblScope>38</biblScope></bibl>
                    </abv:example>
                    <abv:example>
                        <quote>k˳yd dæm fækastī næ card?</quote>
                        <abv:tr xml:lang="ru">
                            <q>как тебе понравилась (буквально „как на тебя посмотрела“) наша
                                жизнь?</q>
                        </abv:tr>
                        <abv:tr xml:lang="en">
                            <q>how did you like (literally "how did our life look at you") our
                                life?</q>
                        </abv:tr>
                    </abv:example>
                    <abv:example>
                        <quote>xorz mæm fækastī</quote>
                        <abv:tr xml:lang="ru">
                            <q>мне понравилась</q>
                        </abv:tr>
                        <abv:tr xml:lang="en">
                            <q>I liked it</q>
                        </abv:tr>
                    </abv:example>
                    <abv:example>
                        <quote>су dæ kæsy?</quote>
                        <abv:tr xml:lang="ru">
                            <q>какое тебе дело?</q>
                        </abv:tr>
                        <abv:tr xml:lang="en">
                            <q>it is none of your business</q>
                        </abv:tr>
                    </abv:example>
                </abv:exampleGrp>
                <re>
                    <note type="comment" xml:lang="ru">Во второй части сложных слов — „наблюдатель“,
                        „сторож“, „пастух“: </note>
                    <note type="comment" xml:lang="en">In the second part of compound words it means
                        „observer“, „watchman“, „shepherd“: </note>
                    <re>
                        <form type="lemma"><orth>dwargæs</orth></form>
                        <sense><abv:tr xml:lang="ru">
                                <q>привратник</q>
                            </abv:tr><abv:tr xml:lang="en">
                                <q>door-keeper</q>
                            </abv:tr></sense>
                    </re>
                    <re>
                        <form type="lemma"><orth>k˳yrojgæs</orth></form>
                        <sense><abv:tr xml:lang="ru">
                                <q>мельник</q>
                            </abv:tr><abv:tr xml:lang="en">
                                <q>miller</q>
                            </abv:tr></sense>
                    </re>
                    <re>
                        <form type="lemma"><orth>qædgæs</orth></form>
                        <sense><abv:tr xml:lang="ru">
                                <q>лесничий</q>
                            </abv:tr><abv:tr xml:lang="en">
                                <q>forest warden</q>
                            </abv:tr></sense>
                    </re>
                    <re>
                        <form type="lemma"><orth>bæxgæs</orth></form>
                        <sense><abv:tr xml:lang="ru">
                                <q>конюх</q>
                            </abv:tr><abv:tr xml:lang="en">
                                <q>stableman</q>
                            </abv:tr></sense>
                    </re>
                    <re>
                        <form type="lemma"><orth>x˳ygæs</orth></form>
                        <sense><abv:tr xml:lang="ru">
                                <q>свинопас</q>
                            </abv:tr><abv:tr xml:lang="en">
                                <q>swine-herd</q>
                            </abv:tr></sense>
                        <note type="comment" xml:lang="ru">и др. (<bibl><ref type="bibl"
                                    target="#ref_РОСл."/><biblScope>607</biblScope></bibl>)</note>
                        <note type="comment" xml:lang="en"/>
                    </re>
                </re>
                <re>
                    <form type="lemma"><orth>kast, bakast</orth></form>
                    <sense><abv:tr xml:lang="ru">
                            <q>взгляд</q>
                        </abv:tr><abv:tr xml:lang="en">
                            <q>look</q>
                        </abv:tr></sense>
                </re>
                <re>
                    <form type="lemma"><orth>ægæs</orth></form>
                    <sense><abv:tr xml:lang="ru">
                            <q>без присмотра</q>
                        </abv:tr><abv:tr xml:lang="en">
                            <q>unguarded</q>
                        </abv:tr></sense>
                </re>
                <re>
                    <note type="comment" xml:lang="ru">Послелог</note>
                    <note type="comment" xml:lang="en">A postposition</note>
                    <form type="lemma"><orth>gæsgæ</orth></form>
                    <sense><sense><abv:tr xml:lang="ru">
                                <q>согласно</q>
                            </abv:tr><abv:tr xml:lang="en">
                                <q>according to</q>
                            </abv:tr></sense><sense><abv:tr xml:lang="ru">
                                <q>по</q>
                            </abv:tr><abv:tr xml:lang="en">
                                <q>in accordance with</q>
                            </abv:tr></sense></sense>
                    <abv:exampleGrp>
                        <abv:example>
                            <quote>mænmæ gæsgæ</quote>
                            <abv:tr xml:lang="ru">
                                <q>по моему мнению</q>
                            </abv:tr>
                            <abv:tr xml:lang="en">
                                <q>in my opinion</q>
                            </abv:tr>
                        </abv:example>
                        <abv:example>
                            <quote>æǧdawmæ gæsgæ</quote>
                            <abv:tr xml:lang="ru">
                                <q>согласно обычаю</q>
                            </abv:tr>
                            <abv:tr xml:lang="en">
                                <q>according to the usual custom</q>
                            </abv:tr>
                        </abv:example>
                        <abv:example>
                            <quote>dæ ʒyrdmæ gæsgæ</quote>
                            <abv:tr xml:lang="ru">
                                <q>по слову твоему</q>
                            </abv:tr>
                            <abv:tr xml:lang="en">
                                <q>according to thy word</q>
                            </abv:tr>
                            <bibl><ref type="bibl" target="#src_Лука"/><biblScope>%i2%i
                                    29</biblScope></bibl>
                        </abv:example>
                    </abv:exampleGrp>
                </re>
                <etym xml:lang="ru">Как и другие употребительные глаголы — иранское наследие. Ср.
                        <mentioned xml:lang="fa"><lang/>
                        <w>bi-kes- %i:%i bi-kas-</w>
                        <gloss><q>смотреть</q></gloss></mentioned> (диал.) (<bibl><ref type="bibl"
                            target="#ref_Жуковский"/><biblScope>I 202</biblScope></bibl>),
                        <mentioned xml:lang="pal"><lang/>
                        <w>nikās dār-</w>
                        <gloss><q>надзирать</q></gloss></mentioned>, <mentioned xml:lang="fa"><lang/>
                        <w>nigāh</w>
                        <gloss><q>взгляд</q></gloss></mentioned>, <mentioned xml:lang="ps"><lang/>
                        <w>kas-, kəs%i:%i katəl</w>
                        <gloss><q>смотреть</q></gloss></mentioned>, <mentioned xml:lang="sgy"><lang/>
                        <w>kas-</w>
                        <gloss><q>смотреть</q></gloss></mentioned>, <mentioned xml:lang="sgy"><w/>
                        <gloss><q>видеть</q></gloss></mentioned>, <mentioned xml:lang="yah"><lang/>
                        <w>ḱas-</w>
                        <gloss><q>смотреть</q></gloss></mentioned>, <mentioned xml:lang="sgh"><lang/>
                        <w>čas-, čes-, čis-</w></mentioned> (<bibl><ref type="bibl"
                            target="#ref_Sköld._Pam."/><biblScope>178, 182</biblScope></bibl>),
                        <mentioned xml:lang="sog-x-chr"><lang/>
                        <w>pcqs-</w>
                        <gloss><q>ждать</q></gloss></mentioned>, <mentioned xml:lang="sog"><lang/>
                        <w>*kas(ks-)</w>
                        <gloss><q>наблюдатель</q></gloss></mentioned>, в %i'nγrks%i ‘астролог’,
                    „наблюдатель звезд“, <mentioned xml:lang="zkh"><lang/>
                        <w>škaš-</w>
                        <gloss><q>смотреть</q></gloss></mentioned>, <mentioned xml:lang="kho"><lang/>
                        <w>kas-</w>
                        <gloss><q>являться</q></gloss></mentioned>, <mentioned xml:lang="ae"><lang/>
                        <w>kas(ākas-)</w>
                        <gloss><q>смотреть</q></gloss></mentioned>, <mentioned xml:lang="sa"><lang/>
                        <w>kāś-</w>
                        <gloss><q>сиять</q></gloss></mentioned>, <mentioned xml:lang="sa"><w/>
                        <gloss><q>смотреть</q></gloss></mentioned>. Может быть, скифское имя
                    %iΚάσαγος%i = ос. %ikæsæg%i ‘смотрящий’. — От этого же корня — <ref type="xr"
                        target="#entry_cæst"/> ‘глаз’. См. также <ref type="xr"
                        target="#entry_fælgæsyn"/> (←%i*pari-kas-%i) ‘смотреть’, <ref type="xr"
                        target="#entry_ængas"/> ‘взгляд’, <ref type="xr" target="#entry_ængæs"/>
                    ‘подобный’ (← %i*han-kasa-%i).%n<bibl><ref type="bibl"
                            target="#ref_Вс._Миллер._ОЭ"/><biblScope>II 46</biblScope></bibl>;
                            <bibl><ref type="bibl" target="#ref_Вс._Миллер._Gr."
                            /><biblScope>57</biblScope></bibl>. — <bibl><ref type="bibl"
                            target="#ref_Hübschmann._Oss."/><biblScope>44</biblScope></bibl>.—
                            <bibl><ref type="bibl" target="#ref_ОЯФ_I"/><biblScope>24,
                            171</biblScope></bibl>.</etym>
                <etym xml:lang="en">It is of Iranian origin as some other generally used verbs. Cf.
                        <mentioned xml:lang="fa"><lang/>
                        <w>bi-kes- %i:%i bi-kas-</w>
                        <gloss><q>to look</q></gloss></mentioned> (<bibl><ref type="bibl"
                            target="#ref_Жуковский"/><biblScope>I 202</biblScope></bibl>),
                        <mentioned xml:lang="pal"><lang/>
                        <w>nikās dār-</w>
                        <gloss><q>to oversee</q></gloss></mentioned>, <mentioned xml:lang="fa"><lang/>
                        <w>nigāh</w>
                        <gloss><q>look</q></gloss></mentioned>, <mentioned xml:lang="ps"><lang/>
                        <w>kas-, kəs%i:%i katəl</w>
                        <gloss><q>to look</q></gloss></mentioned>, <mentioned xml:lang="sgy"><lang/>
                        <w>kas-</w>
                        <gloss><q>to look</q></gloss></mentioned>, <mentioned xml:lang="sgy"><w/>
                        <gloss><q>to see</q></gloss></mentioned>, <mentioned xml:lang="yah"><lang/>
                        <w>ḱas-</w>
                        <gloss><q>to look</q></gloss></mentioned>, <mentioned xml:lang="sgh"><lang/>
                        <w>čas-, čes-, čis-</w></mentioned> (<bibl><ref type="bibl"
                            target="#ref_Sköld._Pam."/><biblScope>178, 182</biblScope></bibl>),
                        <mentioned xml:lang="sog-x-chr"><lang/>
                        <w>pcqs-</w>
                        <gloss><q>to wait</q></gloss></mentioned>, <mentioned xml:lang="sog"><lang/>
                        <w>*kas(ks-)</w>
                        <gloss><q>observer</q></gloss></mentioned>, in %i'nγrks%i ‘astrologer’,
                    „star observer“, <mentioned xml:lang="zkh"><lang/>
                        <w>škaš-</w>
                        <gloss><q>to look</q></gloss></mentioned>, <mentioned xml:lang="kho"><lang/>
                        <w>kas-</w>
                        <gloss><q>to appear</q></gloss></mentioned>, <mentioned xml:lang="ae"><lang/>
                        <w>kas(ākas-)</w>
                        <gloss><q>to look</q></gloss></mentioned>, <mentioned xml:lang="sa"><lang/>
                        <w>kāś-</w>
                        <gloss><q>to shine</q></gloss></mentioned>, <mentioned xml:lang="sa"><w/>
                        <gloss><q>to look</q></gloss></mentioned>. Maybe the Scythian name
                    %iΚάσαγος%i = Ossetic %ikæsæg%i ‘looking’. — The following words is from this
                    root as well: <ref type="xr" target="#entry_cæst"/> ‘eye’. See also <ref
                        type="xr" target="#entry_fælgæsyn"/> (←%i*pari-kas-%i) ‘to look’, <ref
                        type="xr" target="#entry_ængas"/> ‘look’, <ref type="xr"
                        target="#entry_ængæs"/> ‘similar’ (← %i*han-kasa-%i).%n<bibl><ref
                            type="bibl" target="#ref_Вс._Миллер._ОЭ"/><biblScope>II
                        46</biblScope></bibl>; <bibl><ref type="bibl" target="#ref_Вс._Миллер._Gr."
                            /><biblScope>57</biblScope></bibl>. — <bibl><ref type="bibl"
                            target="#ref_Hübschmann._Oss."/><biblScope>44</biblScope></bibl>.—
                            <bibl><ref type="bibl" target="#ref_ОЯФ_I"/><biblScope>24,
                            171</biblScope></bibl>.</etym>
            </entry>
        </body>
